        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 10 at 6:17PM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 617 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Minooka, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Channahon, Minooka, Shorewood, Joliet, Rockdale, and Crest Hill.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
